    <name>
      <text>Using a given displacement time graph to answer the given questions</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
Use the displacement–time graph below to answer the questions.
</p>

[[jsxgraph width="700px" height="450px"]]
var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, {
    boundingbox: [-1, {# d1*1.2 #}, {# t3+1 #}, -5],
    axis: true,
    grid: true,
    showNavigation: false,
    showCopyright: false,
    defaultAxes: {
        y: { name: 'Time (s)', withLabel: true },
        x: { name: '', withLabel: false,  }
    }
});
board.create('text', [-0.8, 0, 'Displacement (m)'], {
    anchorX: 'left',
    anchorY: 'middle',
    rotate: 90
});



var A = board.create('point', [0, 0], {fixed:true, size:2, name:''});
var B = board.create('point', [{# t1 #}, {# d1 #}], {fixed:true, size:2, name:''});
var C = board.create('point', [{# t2 #}, {# d1 #}], {fixed:true, size:2, name:''});
var D = board.create('point', [{# t3 #}, 0], {fixed:true, size:2, name:''});

board.create('segment', [A, B], {strokeWidth:3});
board.create('segment', [B, C], {strokeWidth:3});
board.create('segment', [C, D], {strokeWidth:3});
[[/jsxgraph]]


<hr>

<p><strong>(a)</strong> Describe the motion of the object during each segment.</p>

<p>
Segment A (0 to {@t1@} s):  
[[input:ans1a]] [[validation:ans1a]][[feedback:prt1a]]
</p>

<p>
Segment B ({@t1@} to {@t2@} s):  
[[input:ans1b]] [[validation:ans1b]] [[feedback:prt1b]]
</p>

<p>
Segment C ({@t2@} to {@t3@} s):  
[[input:ans1c]] [[validation:ans1c]][[feedback:prt1c]]
</p>
<hr>

<p><strong>(b)</strong> Calculate the velocity of the object during segment A.</p>
<p>
[[input:ans2]] m/s [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]
</p>

<hr>

<p><strong>(c)</strong> During which segment is the object stationary?</p>
<p>
[[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]
</p>

<hr>

<p><strong>(d)</strong> Calculate the total distance travelled.</p>
<p>
[[input:ans4]] m [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]
</p>

<hr>

<p><strong>(e)</strong> Calculate the average velocity over the whole journey.</p>
<p>
[[input:ans5]] m/s [[validation:ans5]] [[feedback:prt5]]
</p>]]></text>
